      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] fix(reply): let preflight compaction use compaction timeout",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #95553. Required preflight compaction could inherit the outer reply-operation abort signal, so a short reply lifecycle abort window could cancel compaction before the configured compaction timeout had a chance to govern the required preflight work.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis keeps required preflight compaction bounded by the compaction layer while still preserving explicit cancellation. `ReplyOperation` now exposes `explicitAbortSignal`, which aborts for user stop and restart cancellation but does not abort for upstream reply lifecycle cancellation. Required preflight compaction forwards that explicit signal instead of the raw `replyOperation.abortSignal`.\n\nThe patch is intentionally narrow: normal reply runs still use the existing operation abort signal, while only required preflight compaction avoids the lifecycle timeout signal that caused #95553.\n\n## User Impact\n\nWhen a reply needs preflight compaction, users should see compaction complete or fail according to `compaction.timeoutSeconds`, instead of being prematurely canceled by the reply lifecycle abort path. If the user explicitly stops the run or the run is restarted, the preflight compaction still fails closed through the explicit cancellation signal.\n\nThis PR is split out from #95563 to keep the P1 behavior fix reviewable on its own.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-memory.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/reply-run-registry.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner.compaction-safety-timeout.test.ts` passed: 2 auto-reply files / 66 tests and 1 agents file / 22 tests.\n- `corepack pnpm tsgo:core` passed.\n- `git diff --check` passed.\n",
        "branch": "codex/95553-preflight-compaction-timeout",
